OL,6,FHe described Graham, saying: "6ft
OL,7,F3ins, played a heavy game, some of the
OL,8,Fnastiest hands and stick skills we've
OL,9,Fhad in our group. He was one of those
OL,10,Fguys whose ceiling was one of the best
OL,11,FBrits in the league."
OL,13,FCole Shudra, a teammate and close
OL,14,Ffriend of Graham, added: "That was
OL,15,Fprobably one of the hardest moments
OL,16,FI've had in my life. Alex was such a
OL,17,Fclose friend. He was always laughing,
OL,18,Falways joking. He was such a big lad
OL,19,Fbut he was a big teddy bear as well."
OL,21,F"He was like a brother."
